task.summary: MarkdownDoc-1 Fails to resolve document relative path to images.
- Added insert image function. - Fixed bug in settings function that failed to apply settings if no setting file were saved.
- Added InsertLinkFunction. - SaveFunction now opens save dialog!
SaveFunction now only shows .md and .markdown files in save dialog.
- SaveFunction now only shows .md and .markdown files in save dialog. - Copy, cut, and paste functions have been commented out since JEditorPane seems to handle this itself now.
Refactored configuration so that configs are static, but config changed callbacks are per editor window instance. That is, any change to config will affect all open windows.
Bug fix: When settings window were closed by clicking window close button rather than cancel or save neither of these operations were done. Now it is the same as cancel.

- Added PersistentProps API (available from Editor) for loading and saving properties files under {user home}/.markdownDoc. - Finished ExportToPDFFunction, which now also saves the latest generation information for reuse the next time. This uses PersistentProps. - SaveFunction and OpenFunction now also used PersistentProps to save window postition and size on save and reset it on load per filename of edited files.

Saving settings now also saves the window size and position. If there is no known filename at time of settings save, then size and positions is saved as "default" and will thus be loaded and used when a new empty editor window is opened.
Now also exports to html.
- Added support for list bullet indent level change in both directions with tab and shift-tab. - Ran CodeLicenseManager "apply" to insert/update license header information in source files.
The editor is now packaged as: - A clickable, executable Jar file. - A Mac OS X App in a .dmg file.
- Debugged. - Added editor docs.
Added configurable margins.
Now only allows heading to be one line (up to LF/CRLF). Heading where treated like paragraphs before. This change is to be compatible with other Markdown tools.

Added markdown file reading feature by dropping markdown files on editor in preview mode. This will format and show the dropped file without changing the content of the editor. Exiting preview mode will bring you back to the editor content and entering preview mode again will again preview the editor content.
Updated pom.xml to support release to maven central.
Updated pom.xml to support release to maven central.
Updated doc to say that version 1.2.9 is now in maven central.
Updated readme to indicate that version 1.2.9 is now in maven central.
Added support for &, >, and <. Escaping '<' with '\<' does not work in GitHub markdown which made med use &lgt; and > instead, and thus discovered that MarkdownDoc did not support these!
Oops. No longer supprots the MacOS X .app packaging since it worked badly before and not at all in Mavericks. Thereby the link in the README.md file has been removed.

Damn it! The PDFGenerator stupidly converted "<" to "<" and ">" to ">". This should of course have been handled in the MarkdownParser as it is now! Having the PDFGenerator do this translation was truly stupid!
Small edit.
- All code is now annotated with @CompileStatic which will make it compile static also. - Updated for releasing binaries to Bintray.
Set packaging to "pom" for Docs so that it does not produce jars!
Added auto styling to the editing. It turned out to be rather easy, I just had to find the right example of how to do it.

- Added markdown formatting while editing using new MarkdownStyler (loaded with ServiceLoader!). - Refactored the SettingsFunction breaking out the gui into SettingsWindow and also moving out ConfigEditPanel to its own class. The gui is also updated to use a JTabbedPane with a tab for each group. This looks much better and is more manageable.

- Fixed SettingsWindow using a self made LayoutManager to layout the config entries just as I want it. - Bold and Italics function now look if there is selected text and makes the selected text bold or italic. - Insert link now uses any selected text as link text. - It is now possible to enable/disable markdown formatting while writing.

- Fixed SettingsWindow using a self made LayoutManager to layout the config entries just as I want it. - Bold and Italics function now look if there is selected text and makes the selected text bold or italic. - Insert link now uses any selected text as link text. - It is now possible to enable/disable markdown formatting while writing.
- Fixed CompileStatic errors in Groovy code (imports ending in .* does not work in this case!!) - Let CLM update/add source headers.

- Added 3rd toolbar variant. - Refactored the popup windows for image, link, PDF, and HMTL heavily. - Changed how keyboard input is handled between editor and functions. - Can now configure keys in settings.
Regenerated class comment headers with license information.
Changed default preview keyboard shortcut from Ctrl+V (which is paste on windows) to Ctrl+F.
Bug fix: list entries of lower levels than top retained the list char in generated output.
Speedup of styling by disabling styled component while styling.
Now renders a beveled raised border on the popup, making it consistent with other popups.
- Added small popup feedback on save. - Updated documentation.
Updated README.md to point to correct versions of jars and to point at the new place on bintray.
Damn it! Rebuild of editor only regenerated incomplete license.md file!
Updated README.md.
Updated README.md pointing out bintray JCentral for maven artifact availability.
Updated README.md also pointing out MarkdownDocs home on bintray.
Bug fixes.
